January 8, 2007 20:28China News Service, Beijing, January 8 (Correspondent Jin Guolin) Director of the State Administration of Coal Mine Safety Zhao Tiechui said at the January safe production management video conference held today that the administration organs of coal mine safety in China will strengthen the law enforcement on coal mine safety and rigorously pursue responsibilities for accidents this year.He introduced that the situation of safe production of coal mines throughout the country maintained the trend of overall stability and gradual improvement in 2006. This has mainly benefited from a series of effective work, including performance of duties according to the law, continuously enhancing supervision of law compliance; stressing key points in the work, making new progress in management of coal gas; enhancing source management, continuously deepening rectification and closure work; carrying out proper inspection and guidance, enhancing basic safety management by enterprises; rigorously pursuing responsibilities, and strengthening investigation and prosecution of accidents.Zhao Tiechui proposed that around this Spring Festival and March, the nationwide coal mine safety supervision work will put emphasis on implementation of the "supervision plan," continue to strengthen law enforcement, continuously deepen gas management, further push for rectification and closure, strive to consolidate management foundation, implement the entry system, further enhance source management, rigorously pursue responsibilities for accidents, define management responsibilities, and work hard to remove hidden dangers of accidents.